  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, I loved how you compared the app to a cricket game — it made the idea clear! Tell me, did you try adding tomatoes to your moong dal yet?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, I try it yesterday. Tastes good! My mom also like it. Oh, I watch \"3 Idiots\" movie again — still funny. You know that movie?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Nice! Glad the tomatoes worked — and your mom's approval is the best part. '3 Idiots' is a classic. What's your favourite scene?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The scene where all three friends paint the professor's house — iconic! It shows friendship and fun. Also, the \"All is well\" part is so motivational. Do you know that movie? Or maybe you watch Hollywood more?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"You're right — that scene is iconic and full of life! 'All is well' is such a powerful line. I love Bollywood for these moments. Do you prefer Bollywood or Hollywood movies?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, it's a tough choice. I love Bollywood for the music and emotions, but Hollywood has amazing stories and actors. Maybe I like Bollywood more. Have you seen \"RRR\"? Super cool movie!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Bollywood is a big choice — the music and emotions are unmatched! 'RRR' is full of energy and excitement. I agree, it's super cool! What's your favourite part of the movie?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The bike race scene is so intense and fun to watch — those stunts! And the bond between the two main characters is heartening. But honestly, even the small moments like Ram and Raju just being together feel real. Do you watch Bollywood movies?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Bike races and heartening bonds — you really enjoy the emotions in Bollywood! I watch Bollywood often, especially action-comedies. What's your all-time favourite Bollywood film?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara\" is my all-time fave. The travel, music, and bro bond — top class! But honestly, it's hard to pick one. You should try it if you like \"3 Idiots\" and \"RRR.\" Oh, and the songs are bangers. Do you like road-trip movies?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara sounds amazing — I can imagine the travel and music making it unforgettable! Road-trip movies are fun, especially with great songs. Have you watched any recently?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Not recently, but I want to try a road-trip movie in Hindi — maybe something new. \"Barfi!\" is another fav of mine, but it's more drama. Maybe you like that genre too? Gotta go now — thanks for the chat, Maya! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it — 'Barfi!' is a great pick for drama. I'll keep an eye out for new Hindi road-trip films for you. Take care, Priyansh, and tell me how your chicken curry turns out!\""
    }
  ],
